Special Adviser to Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu on Education, Tokunbo Wahab has called for improved security and peaceful co-existence among Nigerians. Wahab stressed that the best birthday gift he wishes to receive are promises of improved security, unity, mutual love, peaceful coexistence and freedom for Nigerians to live in any part of the country. The special adviser, who is 50 today, prayed for an end to bloodletting, even as he worried over the high level of moral decadence and degeneration.   ‘Next president should come from South’     Administrator seeks sustainable environment     ‘Our votes are for Sanwo-Olu, Solaja’   He urged Nigerians to take advantage of their diversity to build a united and stronger country. “At 50, I want to see a country where everything works, where there is love and unity, where there is security of lives and property, where every Nigerian can live in any part of the country without any fear… “At 50, I want to see a new Nigeria with high hope, a nation that is filled with youths that are assured of a better and secured future. I want to see a new country with improved economy, jobs for youths, these are the birthday wishes I cherish more than any gift…” he said.